½ cup Couscous
113 g Baby Tomatoes
2 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
7 g Parsley
56 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
4 tbsp Hummus
1 unit(s) Lemon
250 g Ground Beef
2 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.12 tsp Salt*
0.12 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Plant-based Butter*

Add 2/3 cup (1 1/3 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, halve tomatoes.
Cut cucumbers into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Roughly chop parsley.
Zest, then juice lemon.

Once water is boiling, remove from heat, then add couscous.
Stir to combine. Cover and let stand for 5 min.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp oil, then falafel. (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan. Cook in batches for 4 ppl if needed, using 1 tbsp oil per batch.) Pan-fry until golden-brown, 4-5 min per side. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.
Heat the same pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up beef and stirring often until beef is cooked through, 4-6 min**.

Meanwhile, add half lemon juice, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.
Add spinach, tomatoes, cucumbers and half the parsley. Toss to combine.
Set aside.

Add hummus, red pepper pesto, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water and remaining lemon juice to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.
Set aside.

When couscous is tender, fluff with a fork. Stir in 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) plant-based butter, remaining parsley and lemon zest.
Divide couscous between bowls. Top with falafel and beef.
Divide salad between plates.
Drizzle red pepper hummus sauce over whole plate.

If you've opted to add beef, heat the same pan used to cook the falafel over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up beef and stirring often until beef is cooked through, 4-6 min**.

Divide beef between bowls.